article.headline: Fla. International 67, North Texas 66
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Alex Galindo scored 24 points to lead Florida International to a 67-66 win over North Texas Thursday. FIU (8-10, 3-5 Sun Belt Conference) ended the first half with a 38-37 lead over North Texas (12-6, 3-4). The teams each scored 29 points in the second. The game's score tied and the lead changed seven times. Cedric Essola scored another 12 points for FIU, along with 11 more from Johwen Villegas. The top scorer for North Texas was Calvin Watson with 18 points. Keith Wooden scored 14 points, Michael Sturns scored 11 and Kendrick Davis scored 10. Although the final score was close, North Texas held a 12-point lead with 9:45 left in the first half. FIU's largest lead was 8 points with 18:05 left in the second half.
